President Obama has proclaimed May 15, 2015, as National Defense Transportation Day and May 10 through May 16, 2015, as National Transportation Week. He emphasizes the importance of infrastructure in growing the economy and ensuring safety. However, he notes that America's investment in transportation lags behind other countries, with many major roads and bridges in poor condition. The President is committed to restoring America's infrastructure through investments that will create jobs and improve competitiveness. He also highlights the importance of resilient infrastructure in the face of natural disasters and the need to continue investing in vital transportation networks. Lastly, President Obama calls upon all Americans to recognize the contributions of those who build, operate, and maintain the transportation infrastructure.